<P>
Visits to the morgue can be part of the punishment for young drunken drivers 
under a law signed by Gov. James R. Thompson. 
</P>
<P>
Thompson on Wednesday approved legislation that allows judges to decide whether 
drunken drivers under age 21 should be forced to visit morgues and hospitals to 
see the bodies of people killed in alcohol-related accidents. 
</P>
<P>
"It will leave a lasting impression on young offenders and holds the promise of 
reducing drinking and driving," the governor said in a statement. 
</P>
